The thing about the perjury investigation in Australia is that:
(a) She could be denied entry to Australia or could be arrested on arrival to face perjury charges. 
(b) If she is charged and convicted on perjury charges then her visa can be revoked, and she would be deported.
If deported she would then automatically be denied entry to Australia for some years. 

This is a second offence for her. She broke biosecurity border laws by bring her dogs in. They went easy on her due to the claims she made. It turns out those claims were lies. Perjury. She made it even worse by the mocking of these biosecurity laws - which are taking very seriously in Australia. Which demonstrates that she just doesn't get it. Now they do have more important issues and would probably like to quietly forget about it, however;
(a)	her perjury became international news in her case in London
(b)	when it all happened she picked a verbal fight with the Minster. Which was an absolutely brainless thing to do. Plus the clip is of the Senate Committee so Amber has apparently created a lot more scrutiny from than just the Minister. 
It seems her own poor treatment of so many people has blown her chances of having this swept under the rug. What an idiot. 

If the FBI are in Australia it even raises the question if Australia would seek to extradite Amber. I think this is unlikely but now I don’t think it is as unlikely as I did previously. 

Now all this matters because Aquaman was filmed on the Gold Coast, Australia at the Movie World Studios. You would assume that Aquaman 2 would also be filmed at the same place. If Amber can not travel to and work in, Australia then you would think it would be an easy decision for the company to cancel her contract and drop her from Mera completely. 

So this is not just about some justice. It also potentially sinks her main acting contract.

comment: I am an Australian.  I am not sure what is so surprising about FBI and AFP sharing intel, I am sure the FBI also shares intel with other nations and certainly "allied" nations.  I mean we stand side by side with the USA fighting wars since WWI and our special forces paint targets for US air strikes...  So there is nothing surprising in the coordination.  The problem with evading customs in Australia is that actually our little island we have managed to eradicate the rabies virus entirely and so any animals that can potentially carry the virus being snuck in to Australia is indeed a very serious transgression and I imagine would be even worse had the animals brought that virus in with them, you would expect them to throw the entire book at you if that happened.  We also have very cautious agricultural industry standards to prevent non-native pests from invading and this is why the Australians customs control is one of the most rigorous in the world.  Bringing in any kind of virus by evading and not declaring at customs is considered an act of industrial sabotage against our farming and livestock industries.  But also mocking the government and making posts that show you purgered yourself in court which as mentioned is a criminal act, actually gives them just more reason to come get you.  PS we have extradition treaties with the USA also.
